Photo by Graham Dickie @instadickie / Employees of the pop-up Lucille's 1913, Lawrence Walker and Kimberlin Rivas prepare free meals for communities in need across Houston. Chris Williams started the nonprofit as an offshoot of his acclaimed restaurant Lucille's, which specializes in Southern cuisine. Williams targets facilities that he says are home to "forgotten people"— including many retirement facilities—and tailor-made the menu for the tastes of different neighborhoods, including the Fifth Ward and Sunnyside, where William's own family is from. The kitchen had been preparing several hundred meals five days a week, but lately has scaled back to three days as it ratchets up fundraising efforts.

